SIMPLE: fairly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fairly
<hw>Fair"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a fair manner;
clearly; openly; plainly; fully; distinctly; frankly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Even the nature of Mr. Dimmesdale's disease had never
<qex>fairly</qex> been revealed to him.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Favorably; auspiciously; commodiously; <as>as, a
town <ex>fairly</ex> situated for foreign trade</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Honestly; properly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such means of comfort or even luxury, as lay <qex>fairly</qex>
within their grasp.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Softly; quietly; gently.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fair-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
